As a note, the _encodeURIComponent_ method didn&#39;t encode the parentheses, either.

Just use the _[String.replaceAll](https://262.ecma-international.org/14.0/#sec-string.prototype.replaceall)_ method.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    var string = encodeURIComponent(&quot;tata, abcd &amp; xyz - 1/2kg ()&quot;)
    string = string.replaceAll(&#39;%20&#39;, &#39;+&#39;)

    console.log(string)

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

If you wanted to escape the parentheses, just use the same method.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    var string = encodeURIComponent(&quot;tata, abcd &amp; xyz - 1/2kg ()&quot;)
    string = string.replaceAll(&#39;%20&#39;, &#39;+&#39;)
    string = string.replaceAll(&#39;(&#39;, &#39;%28&#39;)
    string = string.replaceAll(&#39;)&#39;, &#39;%29&#39;)

    console.log(string)

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

And, when you decode the value, make sure to replace the _+_ signs prior to the _decodeURIComponent_ call.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    var string = encodeURIComponent(&quot;tata, abcd &amp; xyz - 1/2kg ()&quot;)
    string = string.replaceAll(&#39;%20&#39;, &#39;+&#39;)
    string = string.replaceAll(&#39;(&#39;, &#39;%28&#39;)
    string = string.replaceAll(&#39;)&#39;, &#39;%29&#39;)

    console.log(string)

    string = string.replaceAll(&#39;+&#39;, &#39; &#39;)
    string = decodeURIComponent(string)

    console.log(string)

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

